1. Goal of This Lab
In this lab you learn how to:
1.	Deploy an application using a Helm chart
2.	Use a private container registry
3.	Upgrade an application to a new chart version
4.	Deploy test and production environments
5.	Configure resource limits and requests
Application used: Etherpad
________________________________________
2. Start the Lab Environment
Command:
lab start packaged-review
What this does
•	Prepares the environment
•	Starts the lab cluster
•	Makes the OpenShift API reachable
•	Resets previous resources
________________________________________
3. Login to the OpenShift Cluster
Command:
oc login -u developer -p developer https://api.ocp4.example.com:6443
Explanation:
Part	Meaning
oc login	login to cluster
-u developer	username
-p developer	password
URL	cluster API server
________________________________________
4. Create Two Projects (Namespaces)
Create development/test project
oc new-project packaged-review
Meaning:
Creates namespace:
packaged-review
Used for testing deployment.
________________________________________
Create production project
oc new-project packaged-review-prod
Namespace:
packaged-review-prod
Used for production deployment.
________________________________________
5. Add Helm Repository
First check existing repos:
helm repo list
Example output:
NAME        URL
do280-repo  http://helm.ocp4.example.com/charts
If missing, add it:
helm repo add do280-repo http://helm.ocp4.example.com/charts
Explanation:
Part	Meaning
helm repo add	add chart repository
do280-repo	repo name
URL	location of charts
Repository stores Helm charts.
________________________________________
6. Search Available Charts
Command:
helm search repo --versions
Output example:
do280-repo/etherpad 0.0.7
do280-repo/etherpad 0.0.6
Meaning:
Two chart versions exist:
0.0.6
0.0.7
________________________________________
7. Examine Chart Configuration
Command:
helm show values do280-repo/etherpad --version 0.0.6
This shows default chart values.
Example:
replicaCount: 1
Meaning:
Default deployment runs 1 pod.
________________________________________
Example image configuration:
image:
  repository: etherpad
  name:
  tag:
Default image:
docker.io/etherpad/etherpad:latest
But the classroom environment is offline, so Docker Hub cannot be used.
________________________________________
8. Use Private Container Registry
Instead of Docker Hub, use:
registry.ocp4.example.com:8443
Image:
registry.ocp4.example.com:8443/etherpad/etherpad:1.8.17
________________________________________
9. Create values-test.yaml
Create file:
values-test.yaml
Content:
image:
  repository: registry.ocp4.example.com:8443/etherpad
  name: etherpad
  tag: 1.8.17
Purpose:
Overrides default image values.
________________________________________
10. Switch to Test Project
Command:
oc project packaged-review
Meaning:
Set active namespace to:
packaged-review
________________________________________
11. Install the Helm Chart
Command:
helm install test do280-repo/etherpad \
-f values-test.yaml --version 0.0.6
Explanation:
Part	Meaning
helm install	install chart
test	release name
do280-repo/etherpad	chart
-f values-test.yaml	custom values
--version 0.0.6	chart version
Helm will create:
•	Deployment
•	Service
•	Route
•	Pod
________________________________________
12. Verify Helm Installation
Command:
helm list
Example output:
NAME  NAMESPACE        CHART
test  packaged-review  etherpad-0.0.6
Meaning:
Release name:
test
Chart version:
0.0.6
________________________________________
13. Check Pod and Deployment
Command:
watch oc get deployments,pods
Output example:
deployment.apps/test-etherpad   1/1
pod/test-etherpad-xxxx          Running
Meaning:
•	Deployment ready
•	Pod running
Press:
CTRL+C
to stop watch.
________________________________________
14. Verify Container Image
Command:
oc describe pods -n packaged-review | egrep '^Name:|Image:'
Output:
Image: registry.ocp4.example.com:8443/etherpad/etherpad:1.8.17
Meaning:
Correct private registry image is used.
________________________________________
15. Get Application URL
Command:
oc get routes
Example output:
test-etherpad-packaged-review.apps.ocp4.example.com
Application URL:
https://test-etherpad-packaged-review.apps.ocp4.example.com
Open in browser.
________________________________________
16. Upgrade Application Version
Update values file:
values-test.yaml
Change image tag:
image:
  repository: registry.ocp4.example.com:8443/etherpad
  name: etherpad
  tag: 1.8.18
________________________________________
17. Verify New Chart Version Exists
Command:
helm search repo --versions etherpad
Output:
0.0.7
0.0.6
________________________________________
18. Upgrade Helm Release
Command:
helm upgrade test do280-repo/etherpad \
-f values-test.yaml --version 0.0.7
Explanation:
Part	Meaning
helm upgrade	update release
test	release name
chart	etherpad
version	0.0.7
Output shows:
REVISION: 2
Meaning deployment updated.
________________________________________
19. Verify Upgrade
Command:
helm list
Output:
etherpad-0.0.7
________________________________________
Check pod image again:
oc describe pods -n packaged-review | egrep '^Name:|Image:'
Output:
1.8.18
New image running.
________________________________________
20. Deploy Production Version
Switch namespace:
oc project packaged-review-prod
________________________________________
Copy values file:
cp values-test.yaml values-prod.yaml
________________________________________
21. Configure Production Route
Edit:
values-prod.yaml
Add route host:
image:
  repository: registry.ocp4.example.com:8443/etherpad
  name: etherpad
  tag: 1.8.18

route:
  host: etherpad.apps.ocp4.example.com
________________________________________
22. Install Production Deployment
Command:
helm install prod do280-repo/etherpad \
-f values-prod.yaml --version 0.0.6
Release name:
prod
Namespace:
packaged-review-prod
________________________________________
Check:
helm list
Output:
prod packaged-review-prod etherpad-0.0.6
________________________________________
23. Verify Production Pod
Command:
watch oc get deployments,pods
Pod should be:
Running
________________________________________
24. Add Resource Limits
Edit:
values-prod.yaml
Add resources:
resources:
  limits:
    memory: 256Mi
  requests:
    memory: 128Mi
Meaning:
Field	Meaning
requests	minimum memory
limits	maximum memory
________________________________________
25. Upgrade Production Deployment
Command:
helm upgrade prod do280-repo/etherpad \
-f values-prod.yaml --version 0.0.7
Now production uses:
chart version 0.0.7
________________________________________
26. Verify Resource Limits
Command:
oc describe pods -n packaged-review-prod | egrep -A1 '^Name:|Limits|Requests'
Output:
Limits:
 memory: 256Mi
Requests:
 memory: 128Mi
Meaning memory limits applied successfully.
________________________________________
27. Compare with Test Deployment
Run:
oc describe pods -n packaged-review
Test deployment has:
no limits
Because values-test.yaml did not define resources.
________________________________________
28. Clean Up Files
Command:
rm values-test.yaml values-prod.yaml
Removes configuration files.
________________________________________
29. Grade Lab
Command:
lab grade packaged-review
This checks if:
•	deployments correct
•	routes correct
•	limits correct
•	chart versions correct
________________________________________
30. Finish Lab
Command:
lab finish packaged-review
Purpose:
•	clean cluster
•	remove resources
•	prepare for next lab
________________________________________
Important Concepts From This Lab
Concept	Meaning
Helm Chart	packaged Kubernetes app
Helm Repo	storage for charts
Release	installed chart
values.yaml	custom configuration
helm install	deploy chart
helm upgrade	update chart
resources.requests	minimum resource
resources.limits	maximum resource
________________________________________
